===message:I agree that war happens because the leaders of the countries that are fighting have something that one or the other wants. I think that wars are useless and that the only thing that they truly accomplish is killing a lot of people that had nothing to do with the start of the war anyway. I think that the soldiers explanation of why wars happen is accurate. One country offends another and the offended country wants to retaliate by gathering all of its allies and fighting. The older soldier was right on the money in my opinion because it is the leaders and not the people who decide to go to war. In some cases pacifism, disarmament, and peaceful negotiations can prevent wars from happening but both sides have to have strong leaders who won't get easily offended by what the other has to offer. Like she stated above I don't believe that those things will ever prevent all wars from happening because everyone wants to be in control of everyone else. The USA is such a wonderful country that people from other places are determined to destroy it. So unfortunately we have to defend ourselves and so begins another war.
